article.headline: Western Michigan 76, Winthrop 71
article.story: TEMPE, Ariz. (AP) -- Ben Reed scored 23 points and Mike Williams added 22 to lead Western Michigan past Winthrop 76-71 Monday in the first round of the azcentral.com Hoops Classic at Arizona State. The Broncos, who have won five straight, on Tuesday will face the winner of the Arizona State-San Diego game played later Monday. Western Michigan (6-1) went 14-2 midway through the first half to get a 36-23 lead. The Broncos led 40-28 at halftime. The Eagles (5-5) never got closer than three in the second half -- when Torrell Martin hit a 20-footer with 33 seconds left -- in losing their third game in a row. Tyrone Walker led the Eagles with 24 points and a career-best 20 rebounds on 9 of 13 shooting, including two 3-pointers. He also had five assists. Reed, who came into the game leading the nation in 3-point shooting percentage (18 of 28), scored 13 of his points in the first half despite missing seven of his first 10 shots. He finished the afternoon 4 of 13 from the field but made 14 of 18 from the free throw line. He made 1 of 3 from beyond the 3-point line. Walker averaged 12.2 points and 6.6 rebounds per game. Walker had 11 points and 11 rebounds in the first half, Torrell Martin added eight, including 2-for-3 on 3-pointers. The Broncos took advantage of 20 Eagle turnovers, scoring 16 points off those mistakes. Winthrop outrebounded Western Michigan 41-30 but made just 23 of 57 field goals.
